<title>USA: CIMA Labs in deal with Bristol-Myers.</title>
<headline>CIMA Labs in deal with Bristol-Myers.</headline>
<dateline>MINNEAPOLIS 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>CIMA Labs Inc said Thursday it introduced its OraSolv dosage form of Bristol-Myers Squibb Co's children's Tempra products in the United States.</p>
<p>Introductory quantities of the product were manufactured at CIMA's Eden Prairie, Minnesota facility.</p>
<p>OraSolv incorporates drugs into tablets that dissolve quickly in the mouth.</p>
<p>CIMA is a drug delivery company that develops and manufactures products based upon its OraSolv technology for marketing by multinational pharmaceutical companies.</p>
<p>((--Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
